016 Scottish Open (snooker)|QF]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#afeeee;\"|[[2017 Scottish Open (snooker)|1R]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#afeeee;\"|[[2018 Scottish Open (snooker)|2R]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#afeeee;\"|[[2019 Scottish Open (snooker)|2R]]\n|-\n|style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\" | [[European Masters (snooker)|European Masters]]<ref group=\"nb\" name=\"EUR\">The event was called the Irish Open (1998/1999) and Malta Cup (2004/2005\u20132007/2008)</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"| LQ\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"| LQ\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"| LQ\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"| LQ\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"| LQ\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"| LQ\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"| NH\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"| LQ\n| colspan=2 style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"|Not Held\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#afeeee;\"|[[2001 European Open (snooker)|1R]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#afeeee;\"|[[2003 European Open (snooker)|1R]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"| LQ\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"| LQ\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"| LQ\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"| LQ\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"|NR\n| colspan=8 style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"| Tournament Not Held\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#ffebcd;\"|[[2016 European Masters|QF]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#afeeee;\"|[[2017 European Masters (snooker)|3R]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#afeeee;\"|[[2018 European Masters|2R]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"| LQ\n|-\n|style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\" | [[German Masters]]<ref group=\"nb\" name=\"GER\">The event was called the German Open (1995/1996\u20131997/1998)</ref>\n| colspan=4 style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"| Tournament Not Held\n| style=\"text-align: