ayers Championship]]<ref group=\"nb\">The event was called the Players Tour Championship Grand Finals (2010/2011\u20132012/2013) and the Players Championship Grand Final (2013/2014\u20132015/2016)</ref>}}\n| colspan=19 style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"| Tournament Not Held\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#afeeee;\"|[[Players Tour Championship 2010/2011 \u2013 Finals|2R]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#afeeee;\"|[[Players Tour Championship 2011/2012 \u2013 Finals|2R]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#afeeee;\"|[[Players Tour Championship 2012/2013 \u2013 Finals|1R]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#afeeee;\"|[[Players Tour Championship 2013/2014 \u2013 Finals|1R]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#ffebcd;\"|[[Players Tour Championship 2014/2015 \u2013 Finals|QF]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#afeeee;\"|[[Players Tour Championship 2015/2016 \u2013 Finals|1R]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"|DNQ\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"|DNQ\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"|DNQ\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"|DNQ\n|-\n|style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\"| [[Gibraltar Open]]\n| colspan=\"24\" style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"| Tournament Not Held\n| style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"|MR\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#afeeee;\"|[[2017 Gibraltar Open|4R]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#afeeee;\"|[[2018 Gibraltar Open|1R]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#afeeee;\"|[[2019 Gibraltar Open|2R]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#afeeee;\"|[[2020 Gibraltar Open|1R]]\n|-\n|style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\"| [[Tour Championship (snooker)|Tour Championship]]\n| colspan=\"27\" style=\"text-align:center; color:#ccc;\"| Tournament Not Held\n|align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"|DNQ\n|align=\"center\" style=\"color:#cccccc;\"|DNQ\n|-\n|style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\" | [[World Snooker Championship|World Championship]]\n| style=\"text-align:c