==External links==\n* {{official website|http://www.bravotv.com/odd-mom-out}}\n* {{IMDb title|4324796}}\n* {{TV Guide|653479}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Odd Mom Out}}\n[[Category:Lists of American sitcom television series episodes]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Odd Mom Out'' episodes}}\n''[[Odd Mom Out]]'' is an American [[comedy]] television series that premiered on June 8, 2015, on [[Bravo (U.S. TV network)|Bravo]].<ref name=\"futon\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/odd-mom-out/listings/|title=Shows A-Z - odd mom out on bravo|work=The Futon Critic|accessdate=September 30, 2016}}</ref> Based on the novel ''Momzillas'', ''Odd Mom Out'' was created by and stars [[Jill Kargman]] as a fictionalized version of herself named Jill Weber, who is forced to navigate the wealthy mommy clique that resides in New York\u2019s prestigious Upper East Side neighborhood. [[Andy Buckley]], KK Glick, [[Sean Kleier]], [[Joanna Cassidy]], and [[Abby Elliott]] also co-star in the series.\n\nOn September 22, 2016, the network renewed ''Odd Mom Out'' for a 10-episode third season shortly after the second season concluded.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Pedersen|first1=Erik|title=\u2018Odd Mom Out\u2019 Gets Season 3 Renewal At Bravo|url=https://deadline.com/2016/09/odd-mom-out-renewed-season-3-bravo-jill-kargman-1201824775/|website=Deadline|accessdate=September 23, 2016|date=September 22, 2016}}</ref>\n\n{{As of|2017|9|13|df=US}}, a total of 30 episodes of ''Odd Mom Out'' have aired.\n\n==Series overview==\n<onlyinclude>{{Series overview\n| color1       = #5BAB66\n| link1        = <includeonly>List of Odd Mom Out episodes</includeonly>#Season 1 (2015)\n| episodes1    = 10\n\n| start1       = {{Start date|2015|6|8}}\n| end1         = {{End date|2015|8|3}}\n\n| color2       = #FDD017\n| link2        = <includeonly>List of Odd Mom Out episodes</includeonly>#Season 2 (2016)\n| episodes2    = 10\n\n| start2       = {{Start date|2016|